===Noun===
'''adumbration'''  (''plural:'' '''[[adumbrations]]''')

# The act of [[adumbrate|adumbrating]], or shadowing forth.
# A faint sketch; an outline; an imperfect portrayal or representation of a thing.
#:''Elegant '''adumbrations''' of sacred truth.''  -Bp. Horsley.
# (Her.) The shadow or outlines of a figure.

